    "Accordingly, increasing evidence shows that metrics are often selected inadequately in image analysis (for example, refs. 2-4).",
    "In the absence of a central information resource, it is common for researchers to resort to popular validation metrics; however, these can be entirely unsuitable, for instance owing to a mismatch of the metric's inherent mathematical properties with the underlying research question and specifications of the dataset at hand (see Fig. 1).",
